<a href="#1" id="1">Credibility object – credibility baseLet {a mathematical formula}A be a set of agent identifiers and {a mathematical formula}P,Q,S ∈ A.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">A credibility object is a pair {a mathematical formula}[P>Q,S] which represents that agent P is strictly more credible than Q, and the agent S is the information source of the credibility element{a mathematical formula}P>Q.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">A credibility base is a finite set {a mathematical formula}C of credibility objects.</a>
